## Layer Conventions

### Controller
{{#if isMicroservice}}
- Lives in `infrastructure/` — thin gRPC adapter only
- One `@GrpcMethod()` per proto RPC, delegates immediately to application service
- No business logic, no error handling — errors bubble up through `RpcExceptionsFilter`
{{else}}
- Owns routes, validation, auth guards, and response metadata
- Should not contain business logic directly
- Delegates work to the service layer
{{/if}}

### Service
{{#if isMicroservice}}
- Lives in `application/` — orchestrates domain/repository logic per use case
- Method names match proto RPCs (e.g. `getOrder` ↔ `rpc GetOrder`)
- Throws `createRpcException(ERROR_CATALOG.ITEM)` for domain errors
{{else}}
- Contains the business logic for each feature
- Handles persistence through repositories and query helpers
- Throws `AppException.from(ERROR_CATALOG.ITEM)` for domain errors
{{/if}}

### Request & Response DTOs
{{#if isMicroservice}}
- **Microservice**: DTOs mirror `.proto` messages — one DTO per RPC request type
  - `GetOrderRequestDto` (with class-validator decorators `@IsString()`, `@IsUUID()`, etc.)
  - Used with `@Payload()` decorator in controller for automatic validation via `RpcValidationPipe`
  - Response types are `.proto` message contracts directly (entities or response DTOs)
{{else}}
- **Monolith**: Traditional HTTP CRUD DTOs
  - `CreateOrderDto`, `UpdateOrderDto` for request bodies
  - `OrderResponseDto` for Swagger/OpenAPI documentation
{{/if}}

### Query Helper
- Files in `queries/` isolate filter and search logic for list endpoints
- Only handles data-access concerns
- The service remains the main orchestration layer
{{#if isMicroservice}}- Not used in microservices (gRPC uses request message fields for filtering){{/if}}

### Module
- Bundles the controller, service, providers, and imports for a feature
- Newly generated features are automatically registered in `AppModule`

## Error Handling Conventions

{{#if isMicroservice}}
- Use `RpcValidationPipe` as the global validation pipe
- Use `RpcExceptionsFilter` as the global exception filter
- Return success payloads that match `.proto` contracts directly (no HTTP envelope)
- The shared error catalog lives in `src/common/errors/rpc-error-catalog.ts`
{{else}}
- Successful responses are wrapped by `ResponseInterceptor`
- Error responses are normalized by `AllExceptionsFilter`
- The shared error catalog lives in `src/common/errors/app-error-catalog.ts`
{{/if}}
{{#if hasUsersModule}}- The users module keeps feature-specific business errors in `user-error-catalog.ts`
{{/if}}{{#if hasAuth}}- The auth module keeps feature-specific business errors in `auth-error-catalog.ts`
{{/if}}- Avoid hardcoding `code` and `message` values inside services
- The helper in `src/common/helpers/database-error.ts` maps database conflicts to application error catalog entries

## Testing Conventions

- The initial scaffold includes unit tests such as `*.service.spec.ts` and `app.controller.spec.ts`
{{#if e2e}}- E2E tests are scaffolded in `test/` and use `jest-e2e.json`
{{else}}- E2E tests are not scaffolded in the current configuration
{{/if}}- Features generated later should follow the same `*.spec.ts` naming convention

